                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                android:text="        Geo-Genius was established by leading academicians with the aim of popularizing the understanding of Geography among the school children. Conducted at the national level, students of grade 2 to 10th can appear for this exam. The Olympiad is conducted every year in two phases. In Phase I, children participate in their respective schools throughout the country. In Phase II, participants with high scores, based on the cut-off, are invited to the National Finals in April. "
